{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769625946,"nonce":"o+hEttF1zdt++0mPHaqTX/z36sI=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87me3ak","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/104","origin":"github"},"title":"Audit and resolve conflicting guidance in agent documentation","message":"## Problem\nReview comments on PR #101 revealed conflicting guidance between `git-hygiene.md` (uses `feature/TASK-` examples) and `issue-first.md` (mandates `feature/ISSUE-` naming). This suggests there may be other conflicts across the documentation.\n\n## Scope\nPerform comprehensive audit of all `.agent/` documentation for:\n\n### 1. Branch Naming Conflicts\n- `git-hygiene.md` shows `feature/TASK-\u003cID\u003e-\u003cdescription\u003e`\n- `issue-first.md` mandates `feature/ISSUE-\u003cnumber\u003e-\u003cdescription\u003e`\n- **Action**: Update git-hygiene.md examples to use ISSUE- pattern\n\n### 2. Script Path Inconsistencies  \n- Some docs reference `script.sh`\n- Others reference `./agent/scripts/script.sh`  \n- Others reference `.\\agent/scripts/script.sh`\n- **Action**: Standardize to `.\\agent/scripts/script.sh` format\n\n### 3. Default Branch Assumptions\n- Some docs assume `main` is always the default branch\n- Project repos may use `jazzy`, `rolling`, or other branches\n- **Action**: Use \"default branch\" terminology, not hardcoded `main`\n\n### 4. Verification Command Syntax\n- Old: `verify_change.sh \u003cpackage\u003e \u003ctype\u003e` (positional args)\n- New: `verify_change.sh --package \u003cname\u003e --type \u003ctype\u003e` (flags)\n- **Action**: Audit all references to verify_change.sh\n\n### 5. Bootstrap vs Setup vs Build\n- Confusion about what each script does\n- **Action**: Clarify in docs:\n  - `bootstrap.sh` = Install ROS/dev tools\n  - `setup.sh` = Clone repos\n  - `build.sh` = Build workspaces\n\n## Deliverables\n- [ ] Create conflict audit report in `.agent/scratchpad/`\n- [ ] List all conflicting statements with file locations\n- [ ] Propose fixes for each conflict\n- [ ] Open follow-up issues for specific fixes\n- [ ] Update git-hygiene.md as immediate priority\n\n## Success Criteria\n- All `.agent/` docs use consistent terminology\n- No conflicting guidance on same topic\n- Single source of truth for each concept\n\n## Priority\n**High** - Conflicting docs confuse agents and reduce workspace reliability\n\nRelated: #101 (glossary PR)","files":null}]}